Direct Known Subclasses:
LearningOpenNode
public class OpenNode
extends Node

This class implements a 'open' node.

A node is open when its purpose has not been fixed. It has no son.

When a tree is created, its root is an open node. The tree is completed when all the open nodes have been replaced by test nodes or leaves.

hasOpenNode

public boolean hasOpenNode()
Description copied from class: Node
Shows if one of the descendants of this node is open. More formally, this function returns true iff this node is open or there exist one son of this node 's' such that s.hasOpenNode() == true.
